request.description:
This endpoint should be used to deliver recordings for verification via a provided URL (fileDownloadURL). All files will be fetched via a simple get request so if the download requires authentication it will need to be in the URL. The fetch has a 15 minute timeout to download and convert the file so it is important that the download speed of the file is good.

This endpoint accepts any FFMPEG compatible file formats and will download and strip just the audio element before verification.  
Body Schema:

```
{ 
//startDate - the date the recording became live 
startDate: string
//endDate - (optional) the date the recording will be taken down 
endDate?: string 
//externalId - (optional) the external id of the sound recording 
externalId?: string 
//organisationId - the ClicknClear id of the organisation who this sound recording belongs to. 
organisationId: number
//fileDownloadURL - a link to the file to be uploaded 
fileDownloadURL: string 
//uploadUseType - how this sound recording will be used 
uploadUseType: "Video On Demand" | "Live Stream" 
//onFinishedMatchingCallBackURL - (optional) an optional call back url which will be called via POST request once the upload has finished the matching process. The shape of the data posted is the same as the Get Revenue Stream Recording Request 
onFinishedMatchingCallBackURL?: string 
}

```

Gets the revenue stream recording by id

Revenue Stream Sound Recording Response Type:

